msContents.summary: Commentary by Ibn Ghāzī on his own mathematical poem; source-text in red with commentary in dark brown.

msItem.title: Bughyat al-ṭullāb fī sharḥ Munyat al-ḥussāb.
بغية الطلاب في شرح منية الحساب

author.persName: Ibn Ghāzī, Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad, 1437 or 1438-1513
Ibn Ghāzī, Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad, 1437 or 1438-1513

msItem.title: Kitāb bughyat al-ṭullāb fī sharḥ munyat al-ḥussāb

supportDesc.extent: i, 164, iii leaves : 202 x 157 (125 x 75) mm, bound to 205 x 170 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Idiosyncratic foliation in ink, upper center recto; modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto; references in the record are to the modern foliation.

layoutDesc.layout: 20 long lines; catchwords each verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī in dark brown ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red; some diagrams and tables.

binding.p: Brownish-red leather over pasteboard with blind-tooled frame; blind-stamped, blue paper onlay mandorla; flap has coordinating onlay.

origin.p: Copy completed on 28 Ramaḍān 1160 AH by ʻAbd al-Qādir ibn Aḥmad (f. 162v).

history.provenance: Acquired by David Eugene Smith on 17 March, 1929 in Marrakesh (note in pencil, first flyleaf recto at front of book: "Marrakech, Mch. 17, 1929. DES.").
